A 50-year-old woman has died after being knocked down in a car park at a tourist spot.
The pedestrian was hit by a bus outside the Trossachs Woollen Mill in Kilmahog by Callander yesterday.
She was airlifted to the Southern General Hospital in Glasgow following the incident at around 6.40pm but later died.
Sergeant Alistair MacLean from Police Scotland said: &quot;This has been a terrible incident which has resulted in the death of a pedestrian.
&quot;I would urge any person who may have witnessed the collision and who has not yet been spoken to by the police to contact us without delay.&quot;
